H.B. 1231
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
May 11, 2026
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH10643-LUe-160A
Short Title: No Voter Registration Changes At DMV. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Ward.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ELIMINATE THE ABILITY TO UPDATE EXISTING VOTER
3 REGISTRATION ON THE DIVISION OF MOTOR VEHICLES' (DMV) WEBSITE OR
4 AT DMV PHYSICAL LOCATIONS AND REQUIRE THAT CHANGES BE MADE AT
5 COUNTY BOARDS OF ELECTIONS.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1. G.S. 163-82.19 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 163-82.19. Voter registration at drivers license offices; coordination on data interface.
9 (a) Voter Registration at Drivers License Offices. – The Division of Motor Vehicles
10 shall, pursuant to the rules adopted by the State Board of Elections, modify its forms so that any
11 eligible person who applies for original issuance, renewal or correction of a drivers license, or
12 special identification card issued under G.S. 20-37.7 may, on a part of the form, complete an
13 application to register to vote, or vote. A voter seeking to update the voter's registration if the
14 voter (i) has changed his or her address or moved from one precinct to another or from one county
15 to another. another or (ii) wants to change the voter's name or party affiliation, shall make those
16 changes at the appropriate county board of elections. The person taking the application shall ask
17 if the applicant is a citizen of the United States. If the applicant states that the applicant is not a
18 citizen of the United States, or declines to answer the question, the person taking the application
19 shall inform the applicant that it is a felony for a person who is not a citizen of the United States
20 to apply to register to vote. The application shall state in clear language the penalty for violation
21 of this section. The necessary forms shall be prescribed by the State Board of Elections. The form
22 must ask for the previous voter registration address of the voter, if any. If a previous address is
23 listed, and it is not in the county of residence of the applicant, the appropriate county board of
24 elections shall treat the application as an authorization to cancel the previous registration and also
25 process it as such under the procedures of G.S. 163-82.9. If a previous address is listed and that
26 address is in the county where the voter applies to register, the application shall be processed as
27 if it had been submitted under G.S. 163-82.9.
28 Registration shall become effective as provided in G.S. 163-82.7. Applications to register to
29 vote accepted at a drivers license office under this section until the deadline established in
30 G.S. 163-82.6(d)(2) shall be treated as timely made for an election, and no person who completes
31 an application at that drivers license office shall be denied the vote in that election for failure to
32 apply earlier than that deadline.
33 All applications shall be forwarded by the Department of Transportation to the appropriate
34 board of elections not later than five business days after the date of acceptance, according to rules
35 which shall be promulgated by the State Board of Elections. Those rules shall provide for a
36 paperless, instant, electronic transfer of applications to the appropriate board of elections.
*DRH10643-LUe-160A*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 …."
2 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies to changes in
3 voter registration occurring on or after that date.
